00:39:16.228 --> 00:39:17.540
AUDIENCE: The two points.

00:39:17.540 --> 00:39:19.040
PROFESSOR: Absolutely.

00:39:19.040 --> 00:39:22.550
That's exactly correct.

00:39:22.550 --> 00:39:25.310
How would you have solved
this on the actual quiz

00:39:25.310 --> 00:39:28.900
if you're not our
brave volunteer?

00:39:28.900 --> 00:39:34.330
Well, that k, if you squint at
it-- not very much actually--

00:39:34.330 --> 00:39:40.200
is pretty much a dot product
between cosine of Pi over 4

00:39:40.200 --> 00:39:41.570
and sine Pi over 4.

00:39:41.570 --> 00:39:43.070
I mean, look at it.

00:39:43.070 --> 00:39:48.310
Remember, if the dot
product of x and z vectors

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:56.550
is x1, z1 plus x2, z2-- so that
basically is x1, z1 plus x2 z2.

00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:59.490
Oh, this should
have been a times.

00:39:59.490 --> 00:40:01.190
Yeah, this should
have been a times.

00:40:01.190 --> 00:40:01.770
Sorry.

00:40:01.770 --> 00:40:03.090
There's a plus there.

00:40:03.090 --> 00:40:05.807
Anyone who missed it
because of that, my bad.

00:40:05.807 --> 00:40:07.140
That's should have been a times.

00:40:07.140 --> 00:40:09.080
That should have been
a times up there.

00:40:09.080 --> 00:40:12.580
It's cosine Pi over 4x cosine
Pi over 4z plus sine Pi

00:40:12.580 --> 00:40:15.260
over 4x times sine Pi over 4z.

00:40:15.260 --> 00:40:17.040
So yeah, it's basically
the dot product

00:40:17.040 --> 00:40:19.420
between cosine Pi over
4x and sine Pi over 4x.

00:40:19.420 --> 00:40:20.930
Bingo.

00:40:20.930 --> 00:40:24.177
All right, last thing.

00:40:24.177 --> 00:40:26.010
Well, we're not done
yet because we're going

00:40:26.010 --> 00:40:27.399
to maybe ask some questions.

00:40:27.399 --> 00:40:29.940
And then we're going to see if
we can calculate those alphas.

00:40:29.940 --> 00:40:33.850
But last thing, let's
