00:46:24.700 --> 00:46:26.520
Just remember, if
they give you a phi,

00:46:26.520 --> 00:46:28.190
do a dot product with it.

00:46:28.190 --> 00:46:29.650
And if they give
you a phi that's

00:46:29.650 --> 00:46:32.820
just one component, dot
product of one component,

00:46:32.820 --> 00:46:34.290
just multiply them together.

00:46:34.290 --> 00:46:34.930
Easy enough.

00:46:34.930 --> 00:46:37.994
If they give you a k,
treat it as a dot product

00:46:37.994 --> 00:46:39.160
and try to reverse engineer.

00:46:39.160 --> 00:46:40.784
It's usually something
like this that's

00:46:40.784 --> 00:46:42.200
easy to reverse engineer.

00:46:42.200 --> 00:46:44.240
I really haven't seen
it where it's not.

00:46:44.240 --> 00:46:48.370
So it often looks like
the scariest problem.

00:46:48.370 --> 00:46:51.690
But it's usually not too bad
to go between phis and k's.

